## Adding New Tasks

1. Define the task in `mise.toml` using the `[tasks."category:name"]` format:

    ```toml
    [tasks."mycat:mytask"]
    description = "What this task does"
    run = "echo hello"
    ```

2. Add the hyphenated target name to the `actions` list in `Makefile`:

    ```makefile
    actions = \
        ...
        mycat-mytask \
        ...
    ```

Naming convention: colons (`:`) in mise, hyphens (`-`) in make.

!!! tip
    Run `mise run mise:setup-completions` to enable shell tab-completion for all mise tasks.
